    "Differences in LLM-as-a-Judge v. SME Evaluation (RQ1 & RQ2)As observed in the results (see Section 5), there is a misalignment between the SMEs and the LLM for both general preference and aspect questions.",
    "Additionally, the findings reveal that the alignment between the SMEs and the LLM varies across different domains, even when an expert persona LLM is used.",
    "To follow, we highlight the major takeaways in the data and discuss reasoning for the variability.7.1.1 Impact of Expert Personas on LLM Alignment with SMEs.",
    "Instructing the model to adopt an expert persona generally improved alignment with SMEs compared to the general model, indicating that expert-level tasks benefit from personified models for evaluation.",
    "The importance of the expert persona is further highlighted by the lower agreement between lay users and the expert persona LLM, as lay users may tend to evaluate or rank outputs based on different criteria [52]."
